Content: {'type': 'text', 'text': 'To measure the improvement brought by the increased ConvNet depth in a fair setting, all our ConvNet layer configurations are designed using the same principles, inspired by Ciresan et al. (2011); Krizhevsky et al. (2012). In this section, we first describe a generic layout of our ConvNet configurations (Sect. 2.1) and then detail the specific configurations used in the evaluation (Sect. 2.2). Our design choices are then discussed and compared to the prior art in Sect. 2.3. ', 'bbox': [169, 205, 826, 277], 'page_idx': 1}

Analysis: The content presents an analytical approach to assessing the effects of increasing the depth of Convolutional Neural Networks (ConvNets) through structured experimentation. The text is organized into sections that outline the general layout of the ConvNet configurations, the specific configurations used for evaluation, and a comparative analysis with prior research. The relationships between the sections are hierarchical, with the layout informing the specific configurations and the discussion reflecting on both. The significance lies in the systematic approach to improving neural network performance while grounding the methodology in established works. Key terms include ConvNet depth, layer configurations, and evaluation methodology.

